commit_message:
Automate OVS bridge creation for multiple mappings

Allows the definition of the global variable OVS_BRIDGE_MAPPINGS (e.g.
in local.conf) to automatically trigger the creation of multiple OVS
bridges. For example:

OVS_BRIDGE_MAPPINGS=physnet1:br-br-enp0s20f1,physnet2:br-enp0s20f2

should automatically yield the creation of two bridges, respectively
associated to the two physical networks declared,
by simply running DevStack with the OVS agent enabled.

Documentation has also been added to doc/source/guides/neutron.rst.

Change-Id: I79dc0213c9d70ba628621c4c0f65481783590085
Closes-Bug: #1535835

Astute uses Ruby 2.1 with YAML 'Psych' engine which is not compatible
with Ruby 1.9 'Psych' engine used by Hierra in Puppet to parse unquoted
strings of passwords started with prefixed numeral values.

This commit uses alternate version of 'YAML::dump' method with forced

commit_message:
Quote "bad" passwords in 'astute.yaml' right before upload it to nodes

Astute uses Ruby 2.1 with YAML 'Psych' engine which is not compatible
with Ruby 1.9 'Psych' engine used by Hierra in Puppet to parse unquoted
strings of passwords started with prefixed numeral values.

This commit uses alternate version of 'YAML::dump' method with forced
quotation of strings according its value and attributes.

Also this commit should fix possible problem with unquoted strings
containing bad mac-addresses which started with two zeros.

This commit should be reverted after upgrading to Ruby 2.1 everywhere.

Change-Id: I7435da01016c4b2266210eb9422ea1fae87de7f8
Closes-Bug: #1494779

commit_message:
CSR should contain the sig-alg object in openssl >= ver 1.0.1i

In the older openssl versions the signature algorithm object in csr
is by default set to itu-t; However in the versions 1.0.1i and later
it should be set explicitly.

Closes-Bug: #1538296
Change-Id: I84d7ea57dd93b5f278aa8d0dfddd9d870aa6e061

commit_message:
LBAAS-2006 Remove Foreign Key constraint during ALTER

Beginning with MySQL 5.6, ALTER will fail if there are foreign key
constraints affecting the column being altered.  This patch
removes the constraint, before applying the update and then
restores the constraint.

Change-Id: Iabbd183a0c1b527806c5d9214c7305c8c22e3732

revisions:
[{'number': 2, 'created': '2016-02-10 22:03:05.000000000', 'files': ['cinder/volume/manager.py', 'cinder/volume/driver.py'], 'message': "Pass a host's volumes to the driver upon fail-over

Where grouping all of a Cinder backend's replicated volumes on a storage
array is not possible, vendors will need a list of volumes from the
manager at fail-over time in order to identify which volumes to fail-over.
This list should include all volumes that belong to the Cinder backend we
are failing-over.

With these volumes, a driver will then be able to determine which ones are
replicated (whether that is by volume type or all the volumes on the
backend) and fail-over each replicated volume individually.

This prevents drivers from accessing the Cinder database directly to
retrieve this list, as well as provides a solution for those who cannot
query their storage array to find all replicated volumes that belong to
a specific Cinder host on a specific OpenStack deployment.

Change-Id: I6b8e5fab96faad3298c2c193a14c6110db9fce48
"}]
commit_message:
Pass a host's volumes to the driver upon fail-over

Where grouping all of a Cinder backend's replicated volumes on a storage
array is not possible, vendors will need a list of volumes from the
manager at fail-over time in order to identify which volumes to fail-over.
This list should include all volumes that belong to the Cinder backend we
are failing-over.

With these volumes, a driver will then be able to determine which ones are
replicated (whether that is by volume type or all the volumes on the
backend) and fail-over each replicated volume individually.

This prevents drivers from accessing the Cinder database directly to
retrieve this list, as well as provides a solution for those who cannot
query their storage array to find all replicated volumes that belong to
a specific Cinder host on a specific OpenStack deployment.

Change-Id: I6b8e5fab96faad3298c2c193a14c6110db9fce48

[{'number': 2, 'created': '2016-01-27 18:20:55.000000000', 'files': ['barbican/tests/plugin/crypto/test_p11_crypto.py', 'barbican/plugin/crypto/pkcs11.py', 'barbican/tests/plugin/crypto/test_pkcs11.py'], 'message': 'Remove padding from legacy stored secrets

The old PKCS11 module padded secrets to the AES block length before
encryption. The new PKCS11 module does not pad secrets that it encrypts
and needs to detect old secrets and remove the padding before returning
the decrypted data. This commit implements that checking and pad
removal.

'}]
commit_message:
Remove padding from legacy stored secrets

The old PKCS11 module padded secrets to the AES block length before
encryption. The new PKCS11 module does not pad secrets that it encrypts
and needs to detect old secrets and remove the padding before returning
the decrypted data. This commit implements that checking and pad
removal.

Closes-Bug: 1536384
Change-Id: If8239a9d10c17ebf27ef1ac481b1bf9042968a62

commit_message:
Creation of neutron::db::sync

In order to standardize the way dbsync are run across our modules,
we create a new class neutron::db::sync.
This class will be included if sync_db is enabled.

By making this transition the neutron::db::sync class
can be returned by the ENC.

A use case would be in an highly available environment with 3 galera
nodes, include neutron::server on every node with sync_db set to false
and have the ENC return ceilometer::db::sync just for one node.

Change-Id: I81e824e3e9e8f901b2a0084c7a5ec42c53781864
(cherry picked from commit 6d4ff50c5b448f6604d08e1bb2c739ac6aecc857)

commit_message:
Support setting instance_user to an empty string

This deals with the case where you don't want heat setting instance_user
for you. See
http://lists.openstack.org/pipermail/openstack-dev/2015-June/068333.html
for details.

Closes-Bug: #1472053

Change-Id: I9e8be0dd50709d271fc81683770c78380724e405

commit_message:
Assign load_balancer in _port_to_vip()

In _port_to_vip() which will be called by allocate_vip() it didn't
assign value to vip.load_balancer. This caused a exception in the
revert path in deallocate_vip(), which used vip.load_balancer.id

Change-Id: I31770e331edc1511385c3ba334afce6fc8af271c

commit_message:
Devstack: create endpoint in catalog unconditionally

The KEYSTONE_CATALOG_BACKEND is being deprecated, and as such we should
just always create the ironic endpoint in the service catalog. Remove
the conditional here.

See also:
http://lists.openstack.org/pipermail/openstack-dev/2016-February/086272.html

Change-Id: I2d47ebe13a23bd39648cc09c72dc975ccadd64d4

commit_message:
Set unprovision and active timeout to match build_timeout

The build_timeout for the ironic baremetal build is at
340s. Modify the unprovision_timeout and active_timeout
to match BUILD_TIMEOUT to avoid frequent failures during
IPA gate jobs.

Change-Id: Idfdc54210e33c71719c7fd0c905d0b802809e173
Related-Bug: #1393099

commit_message:
Fix liberty Neutron client incompatiblity

NeutronMixin is expecting at least one keyword argument in the
Neutron list resource function. This is not always the case as
the Neutron extension overwrite the function with **params.

This patchset is to pass a keyword argument instead of a dictionary
to the list resource function

Change-Id: Iaf68481e4cce9100f129f095d3057ad5cb7c4a13
Closes-bug: #1540563

Moves nested quotas closer to a usable state by:
  * Disabling -1 limits in child projects until a fix for those land
  * Pushing the logic of checking for parent down into the quota driver
  * Not silencing failure to get_project from Keystone

This patch also has some consequences that should not be overlooked,
for instance if a deployment is using Keystone v3 "get_project" must

commit_message:
WIP Fix enforcement of default child quota values

Moves nested quotas closer to a usable state by:
  * Disabling -1 limits in child projects until a fix for those land
  * Pushing the logic of checking for parent down into the quota driver
  * Not silencing failure to get_project from Keystone

This patch also has some consequences that should not be overlooked,
for instance if a deployment is using Keystone v3 "get_project" must
be able to performed for the current project before *any* quota related
operations can be performed (including create volume).  This is required
for keeping quotas in a good state, and it will not affect anyone on
with only Keystone v2 deployments.

The last point to note is this patch will not fix any existing
deployments which have "allocated" quota in DB in an incorrect state
from using the current nested quota code with limits=-1.

Change-Id: I5cf03494d0f1eb22dd6b998ee04a229da6c4da52

commit_message:
Use custom repos for Ubuntu bootstrap image

The issue is that fuel-createmirror creates
partial mirror which does not follow
ubuntu repository structure practice.
It puts all necessary packages under main
section. It does create only one suite
(not suite-security, suite-updates).
This patch makes it possible to use such custom
mirrors giving to a user possibility to
define not only mirror root url
but also the list of suites: e.g. 'trusty trusty-updates'
as well as the list of sections: e.g. 'main restricted'.

Closes-Bug: #1486551
Change-Id: I532d8ef5e8d5a02f10e9bb07bcacfd904db3d23e

revisions:
[{'number': 1, 'created': '2016-01-20 00:22:38.000000000', 'files': ['cinder/api/contrib/quotas.py', 'cinder/tests/unit/test_quota.py', 'cinder/quota.py'], 'message': 'WIP Enforce child quota default values

POC to show how default child quotas can be fixed
by changing Keystone policy.json to allow admin_or_member to
retrieve projects, and then grabbing the project in the create_volume
path as well. A complete fix will involve:
* modifying policy.json in Keystone repo
* caching the project heirarchies on the Cinder side
* refactoring the quota mgmt commands so that get_project isn't called twice
* moving project helpers out of cinder/api/conrtib/quotas.py

For this POC to work, add the following rule to Keystone's policy.json:
    "admin_or_member":  "is_admin:True or project_id:%(project_id)s",
and modify the get_project line to be the following:
    "identity:get_project": "rule:admin_or_member",

Change-Id: I4feb1abe82b72744231e81b4e74a8f7b6ec02a86
'}]
commit_message:
WIP Enforce child quota default values

POC to show how default child quotas can be fixed
by changing Keystone policy.json to allow admin_or_member to
retrieve projects, and then grabbing the project in the create_volume
path as well. A complete fix will involve:
* modifying policy.json in Keystone repo
* caching the project heirarchies on the Cinder side
* refactoring the quota mgmt commands so that get_project isn't called twice
* moving project helpers out of cinder/api/conrtib/quotas.py

For this POC to work, add the following rule to Keystone's policy.json:
    "admin_or_member":  "is_admin:True or project_id:%(project_id)s",
and modify the get_project line to be the following:
    "identity:get_project": "rule:admin_or_member",

Change-Id: I4feb1abe82b72744231e81b4e74a8f7b6ec02a86

commit_message:
WIP Fix child default quota to enforce policy

Just a proof of concept for what it might look like to
use "cinder" user with the "service" tenant to allow project retrieval.
This requires giving "cinder" admin priveledges in "service" project.
Haven't yet done any of the larger cleanup / unit test cleanup we'd want
if we actually went this route.

commit_message:
LeftHand: Implement un/manage snapshot support

Implements support for managing and unmanaging snapshots to
the HPE LeftHand driver.

This patch now allows snapshots to be removed from OpenStack
management but still left on the LeftHand backend. Snapshots
on the LeftHand backend can also be managed by OpenStack.

DocImpact
Implements: blueprint lefthand-manage-unmanage-snapshot
Change-Id: Ic0048fd5da437cf8caddc166cf60ec035def39aa

subject: Make Server user_data update policy configurable
revisions:
[{'number': 3, 'created': '2016-02-10 14:27:58.000000000', 'files': ['heat/engine/resources/openstack/nova/server.py', 'heat/tests/openstack/nova/test_server.py', 'heat/common/config.py'], 'message': 'Make Server user_data update policy configurable

Currently when managing a group of Servers, you have no choice but to
destroy all of them for any change to the server user_data, even if
you only want to pass that userdata to new instances (such as adding
per-node data during a stack-update which isn't needed by the existing
nodes).

So, instead add a new config option default_user_data_update_policy
which enables forcing "IGNORE" so any changes to user_data are ignored
on update, with the current behavior maintained by the default of
"REPLACE".

In a subsequent patch a new user_data_update_policy property will be
added similar to those which already exist for flavor/image, but this
patch is proposed initially as so it may be considered as a backportable
(required to fix to address TripleO update issues).

Change-Id: I29a2b846f02d5ccdd29b666ed084333580b77465
Partial-Bug: #1539541
'}]
commit_message:
Make Server user_data update policy configurable

Currently when managing a group of Servers, you have no choice but to
destroy all of them for any change to the server user_data, even if
you only want to pass that userdata to new instances (such as adding
per-node data during a stack-update which isn't needed by the existing
nodes).

So, instead add a new config option default_user_data_update_policy
which enables forcing "IGNORE" so any changes to user_data are ignored
on update, with the current behavior maintained by the default of
"REPLACE".

In a subsequent patch a new user_data_update_policy property will be
added similar to those which already exist for flavor/image, but this
patch is proposed initially as so it may be considered as a backportable
(required to fix to address TripleO update issues).

Change-Id: I29a2b846f02d5ccdd29b666ed084333580b77465
Partial-Bug: #1539541

commit_message:
Add a note about rerunning the installer

Add a note saying the installer can be rerun to reapply changes that
have been made in undercloud.conf. This is a potentially dangerous
operation if an overcloud has already been deployed or a deployment is
in progress.

Change-Id: I628dbe836a6d798b7d8e6232cde7d9c99ab9b1ee

subject: Use Client-ID in devstack ping request to Zaqar
revisions:
[{'number': 2, 'created': '2016-02-10 20:34:32.000000000', 'files': ['devstack/plugin.sh'], 'message': 'Use Client-ID in devstack ping request to Zaqar

With the recently merged patch https://review.openstack.org/274972,
Zaqar now requires "Client-ID" header for API v2.

Our devstack plugin checks if Zaqar has started by sending request to
Zaqar's ping endpoint. But devstack plugin is not using "Client-ID"
header for sending this request, so the request now always fails and
devstack thinks that Zaqar service hasn't started.

This patch adds "Client-ID" header to the ping request to Zaqar in the
devstack plugin.

Change-Id: I441a5a9778d0676e0a380f5e20be40e1a029409f
'}]
commit_message:
Use Client-ID in devstack ping request to Zaqar

With the recently merged patch https://review.openstack.org/274972,
Zaqar now requires "Client-ID" header for API v2.

Our devstack plugin checks if Zaqar has started by sending request to
Zaqar's ping endpoint. But devstack plugin is not using "Client-ID"
header for sending this request, so the request now always fails and
devstack thinks that Zaqar service hasn't started.

This patch adds "Client-ID" header to the ping request to Zaqar in the
devstack plugin.

Change-Id: I441a5a9778d0676e0a380f5e20be40e1a029409f

commit_message:
scp/ssh do not check for know host keys

Not every ssh/scp command used the SSH_OPTIONS which
could lead to know host key questions with interactive
shells.

SSH_OPTIONS also extended with a conection retry option,
just in case.

SSHOPTS also replaced with SSH_OPTIONS.

'scr -r' was replaced with 'tar|ssh' for coping tripleo-common,
it is expected to be faster.

Change-Id: I664de59ec930052f84b4b15990f24bac4826f539

commit_message:
Pass -q option to yum

The maximum payload size of the return signal from a Heat software
deployment is 1MB, and the output of yum starts breaking this limit at
~1000 packages to update - which is not an atypical number. To prevent
this, pass the -q (quiet) option to reduce the amount of output to a
manageable level.

Change-Id: I517271e8465885421a78b73c5af756816c37a977
Resolves-rhbz: #1304878
Closes-Bug: #1543034

commit_message:
Set 'host' globally in Cinder instead of per-backend basis

This change will set a common value for 'host' across all
controllers. We missed to do so for the NFS backend previously.

It will still be possible to set a different per-backend 'host'
value by providing it via ExtraData.

Change-Id: I00fd05660a15be3611e1a394650be6ab713670f9

subject: app,command: disallow abbrev by default
revisions:
[{'number': 4, 'created': '2016-01-11 10:27:12.000000000', 'files': ['cliff/app.py', 'cliff/tests/test_app.py', 'cliff/command.py'], 'message': "app,command: disallow abbrev by default

By default, abbrev support is enabled in argparse, which can mangle
cliff arguments as shown in the test since all the arguments from all
the commands are not registered at once in the parser, but are parsed in
multiple passes.

It's a nasty behaviour that by default can break application using cliff
without having them noticing. Since I don't think anyone is really
relying on the abbrev behaviour for real, let's just disable it
altogether.

Depends-On: I903ce9564a83d3ee69f4efeb726d3c2d3ff69bbb
Change-Id: I77127e364e938418de36b09c0b80644b77d62336

commit_message:
app,command: disallow abbrev by default

By default, abbrev support is enabled in argparse, which can mangle
cliff arguments as shown in the test since all the arguments from all
the commands are not registered at once in the parser, but are parsed in
multiple passes.

It's a nasty behaviour that by default can break application using cliff
without having them noticing. Since I don't think anyone is really
relying on the abbrev behaviour for real, let's just disable it
altogether.

Depends-On: I903ce9564a83d3ee69f4efeb726d3c2d3ff69bbb
Change-Id: I77127e364e938418de36b09c0b80644b77d62336

commit_message:
Remove tripleoclient.baremetal wrapper

The Ironic client now supports the OSC plugin interface directly, so
this wrapper is no longer needed. Removing it will allow us to specify
which Ironic API version to use via the standard mechanisms.

commit_message:
Modify test workaround for extra_dhcp_opts

The neutron create API now returns extra_dhcp_opts. In older versions
it did not so it had to be removed when comparing the port definitions
between the "create" and the "get". Now we only remove it if it is not
present in the "create". This keeps it working for our keystonev2 test
job which runs against stable/liberty now.

Change-Id: I4d6a57b0f15f1868c5ba4e62a2bf248662bd8896

subject: Volume support for multi hypervisors
revisions:
[{'number': 1, 'created': '2015-12-01 21:00:49.000000000', 'files': ['specs/mitaka/volume-support-for-multi-hypervisors.rst'], 'message': "Volume support for multi hypervisors

In multi hypervisor OpenStack environment using such as
KVM, VMware, Hyper-V etc, we need to provide Cinder storage
backends corresponding to these hypervisors for booting an
instance from a volume. For example, VMware needs VMDK Cinder
backend, Hyper-V needs Windows Cinder backend and also KVM needs
supported backends such as LVM, ceph etc. KVM can't boot from
VMDK backend.

However, there is no way to specify storage backend when we boot
an instance from a volume. As a result, the boot volume might be
created on unrelated backend then the volume boot will fail.

To boot an instance from specific combination between hypervisor
and storage backend, Nova should pass hypervisor_type as a hint
of Cinder filter scheduler when Nova creates a new volume for
attaching the instance.

DocImpact
Blueprint: volume-support-for-multi-hypervisors
Change-Id: I53f62a8c75e303361ded14f2f4bd6072af666bf0
"}]
commit_message:
Volume support for multi hypervisors

In multi hypervisor OpenStack environment using such as
KVM, VMware, Hyper-V etc, we need to provide Cinder storage
backends corresponding to these hypervisors for booting an
instance from a volume. For example, VMware needs VMDK Cinder
backend, Hyper-V needs Windows Cinder backend and also KVM needs
supported backends such as LVM, ceph etc. KVM can't boot from
VMDK backend.

However, there is no way to specify storage backend when we boot
an instance from a volume. As a result, the boot volume might be
created on unrelated backend then the volume boot will fail.

To boot an instance from specific combination between hypervisor
and storage backend, Nova should pass hypervisor_type as a hint
of Cinder filter scheduler when Nova creates a new volume for
attaching the instance.

DocImpact
Blueprint: volume-support-for-multi-hypervisors
Change-Id: I53f62a8c75e303361ded14f2f4bd6072af666bf0

commit_message:
Make pep8 *the* linting interface

According to the PTI (=Python Test Interface,
http://governance.openstack.org/reference/cti/python_cti.html), pep8
is the interface for codestyle checks. Move all tests from linters to
pep8.

This change will be followed by a change to project-config to use pep8
for testing in the gate.

Note that the deps line is not needed, pep8 will use the default
environment.

Change-Id: I791b6f6e073e316e4e11867493647c917350eb4f

commit_message:
Fix endpoint names

The commit daad3d4224f12d2c23c41a70cdf522e7c55536ba added a bunch of new
endpoints, but failed to use the new input data in calculating the
outputs: the GlanceRegistry ones use the Glance endpoints and the
Horizon one the Heat endpoint. This would cause anything querying these
endpoints from the endpoints map to get the wrong ports.

Change-Id: I8e1780b26e285187142be41b4f3aae3efe7eaaee

commit_message:
Add filter for do_package_list

Previously, do_package_list only supported 'limit' and 'include-disabled'.
With this change,  filters that include  'search', 'name','fqn','type',
'category', 'owned', 'tag', and 'class_name' are supported.

Change-Id: I1350b7c27157aaaa04053c61e8fead4c9c639ea9
Closes-Bug:#1536934

commit_message:
Replace HTTP 415 return code to HTTP 406 when it's correct

Server must return HTTP 406 code when content type,
specified in "Accept" header unexpected or unknown
Otherwise server must return HTTP 415 code.
For example, if content type parsed from "Content-Type"

Change-Id: Ic85d1ad9e44ae722dca347b9f1dd643ba3490062
Closes-Bug: #1512390

commit_message:
Port over pretty_tox.sh from nova-powervm

nova-powervm has a bash script that uses the ostestr package to
format the output from tox in a 'pretty' format. It makes it
much more readable. pretty_tox.sh is pulled from Nova and
nova-powervm as-is and enabled in tox.ini.

Change-Id: I9e90c4d595b95ae02be244163f27d87409e3a078

commit_message:
Set conditions for devstack-dsvm and python34 on freezer

The gate-freezer-devstack-dsvm and
gate-freezer*-python34 now are executed
against any branch but stable/kilo for the all
the freezer* repos.

This is needed because in stable/kilo the devstack
plugin is not currently backported and because
freezer stable/kilo is incompatible with python3.4

Change-Id: I8bd6d4cad899b503166dbfb6823eb593d642e4a4

commit_message:
Add new test_rebuild_instance_with_volume to cells exclude list

This commit adds a newly added tempest test to the cells exclude list.
The test is always failing on cells and it's because it's doing
operations that don't work with cells turned on. So lets exclude it
for now. Ideally all this skip logic will be in the tempest config and
we don't have to do this anymore.

Closes-Bug: #1543253
Change-Id: Ic9db51a41f95b0d18f97745a0da7e99fdfa21e51

commit_message:
Change global requirements forcing cliff!=1.16.0

commit_message:
Fix the broken link in devref docs

The link to Dashboard is broken in the generated docuemnt
http://docs.openstack.org/developer/neutron/
This patch fixes it and addresses warnings so that
tox -e docs works.

Also add a reference to Gerrit Dashboard Creator
so that developers can customize it to what they want.

Change-Id: Ic45ab48e68af9e5e8255161fe9eb2354ae124f50

commit_message:
Vagrant: Generify post-config options for DevStack

Generify post-config options for DevStack. On the controller
node, enable two DHCP servers per neutron subnet by default.
On the compute nodes, remove prior enabling of DHCP agent to
provide metadata instances because change-id
Ib99b42adb19a92b9af9c685fb2d8f6f0f9fd8315 enables it by
default in DevStack.

Change-Id: I1e4486ed5e646a2c17a448f86023df3b32e6a099

subject: Support stable requirements
revisions:
[{'number': 1, 'created': '2016-02-08 19:48:12.000000000', 'files': ['jenkins/scripts/project-requirements-change.py'], 'message': "Support stable requirements

project-requirements-change.py master runs against stable branches
with the stable version of requirements. requirements provides the
Requirement class that's used by project-requirements-change.py. The
stable version of the Requirement class doesn't have the `extras`
attribute, which was added in commit 33636c1d.

The workaround is to check if the Requirements object has extras and
only use extras if present.

Change-Id: I90839386dff7f28e6fa8ca7c4c56b547eaa7a541
"}]
commit_message:
Support stable requirements

project-requirements-change.py master runs against stable branches
with the stable version of requirements. requirements provides the
Requirement class that's used by project-requirements-change.py. The
stable version of the Requirement class doesn't have the `extras`
attribute, which was added in commit 33636c1d.

The workaround is to check if the Requirements object has extras and
only use extras if present.

Change-Id: I90839386dff7f28e6fa8ca7c4c56b547eaa7a541

commit_message:
Refactor ovn_nb_sync.OvnNbSynchronizer

In the present implementation there are some problems
 - AttributeError exceptions are seen when run in 'repair' mode
 - delete lport in ovn nb db is failing during sync for ports
   which are in ovn nb db but not in neutron db. This is because
   to delete an lport, lswitch information is required.

This patch refactors the ovn_nb_sync.OvnNbSynchronizer and
fixes all these issues.

Closes-bug: #1542182
Change-Id: Ib200a1c9670e0119691c0477ee4920ac173b73c8

commit_message:
Don't overwrite original traceback in certain cases of i9n failures

Achieve this by muffling exceptions (raised due to Selenium became not
resposive) while taking integration test failure screenshot.

Also extract the pattern of muffling and capturing exceptions common
for dump_browser_log, dump_html_page and save_screenshot in a common
@exceptions_captured context manager.

commit_message:
ports & networks gather should validate existance

_gather_port_ids_and_networks assumes that the input networks variable
doesn't contain the networks in ifaces. This is a wrong assumption
ever since the introduction of the "refresh_cache-<instance id>" locks to
the process in the Liberty cycle (see related bugs) and the
"Refactor network API 'get_instance_nw_info'" patchset
(https://review.openstack.org/#/c/146036/).

The fix validates that the networks stated in ifaces doen't exist in the
gotten networks list.

Duplicate networks were observed at the following closed/related bugs.

Change-Id: I8c2c9e3c89babbe5e48c5129b9854013690b38f6
Closes-Bug: #1522112
Related-Bug: #1467581
Related-Bug: #1501735
(cherry picked from commit 3031adb857993d8196b4c9febca51ac82cf35fd6)

commit_message:
Add a tool for reserving migration placeholders during release time

This adds a tool to make it easy to reserve placeholder migrations
after we do a release. This is something we have to do each time we
do a release, and it can be somewhat silly in terms of mechanical
work. This adds a script to make it trivially easy.

Change-Id: I34c11f1aee64ad36887779f1c9ca4491a25580ec

commit_message:
Add metadefs for Cinder volume type configuration

The following Cinder patch adds support to specify Cinder volume type
via cinder_img_volume_type parameter in glance properties on image
metadata. The property should be added in the Metadata Definitions
catalog.

https://review.openstack.org/#/c/258649/

DocImpact: Add cinder_img_volume_type to Image service property
           keys list at CLI reference.
           http://docs.openstack.org/cli-reference/glance.html
Change-Id: I3bbb20fdf153e12b7461fa9ea9fa172a8d603093
Depends-On: I62f02d817d84d3a7b651db36d7297299b1af2fe3

commit_message:
Add better help text to scheduler options (5)

The previous commit moved all the scheduler options to a central
location. This commit adds additional help text to those options.
Because of the large number of options, the improved help text will be
split into several patches; this is patch 5 of 7.

Blueprint centralize-config-options

Change-Id: Iac694747a219ed690f8d75068982df8cbecae28b
